data.description: You won't want to miss this opportunity to fall in love with this beautiful 3 Bedroom 2.5 Bath Colonial home in the sought after Southwood Crossing development. The first floor makes living easy with a bright living room that looks into the spacious kitchen and dining area, and a convenient half bath. The one car garage leads into the kitchen making grocery trips a breeze. The second floor has two good sized bedrooms with a hall full bath, and a relaxing primary suite with its private bath featuring a two sink vanity. Need more room? You'll find it in the spacious unfinished basement with lots of room for storage or to finish, and houses the utilities including a new the AC compressor, washer and dryer hook ups, a passive radon pipe, newer water-proofing system and an egress window. The entire yard is beautifully landscaped and the backyard is wrapped with elegant black iron fencing. The fenced backyard also includes a raised bed garden and flower beds, a fish pond, a stone fire pit and a pergola covering the concrete patio. Why wait to build when this one is ready to go with lots of extras! Located in the Shippensburg school district and close to Shippensburg University and the Luhrs Performing Arts Center with easy access to Rt 11 and I81 for commuting and close to unique amenities such as Cumberland Valley Rail-Trail and Appalachian Trail, lots of shopping and medical facilities, golf and more!
